In article &lt;3033@rouge.usl.edu&gt; pml@cacs.usl.edu (Patrick M. Landry) writes:
&gt;I am hoping someone has already done this so I won't have to figure it
&gt;out. Since installing bind on 95% of the hosts here I have gotten out
&gt;of the habit of updating the /etc/hosts file on those machines which
&gt;still need it. I am looking for a program which will query bind and 
&gt;create a /etc/hosts file. I am sure other people have thought of this
&gt;but am not sure if it is doable. (doable?)

It is doable. If I can just get enough free time so I can complete the
man page, I could release a beta version of my bind query program.
It can apart from doing normal queries, generate /etc/hosts and HOSTS.TXT
files.
Though I only knows that it works on a Sun.

   Dan

